# Python code formatting and linting rules for Cursor

## Code Formatting
- Use `ruff format` to format code (handles trailing spaces, indentation, etc.)
- Use `ruff check --fix` to auto-fix linting issues
- Maximum line length: 100 characters
- Use double quotes for strings
- Remove trailing whitespace from all lines

## Before committing
Run: `ruff format . && ruff check --fix .`

## Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 conventions
- Use type hints where possible
- Keep docstrings concise and clear
- Remove trailing whitespace
- Use consistent indentation (4 spaces)

## Virtual Environment Usage
- This project uses a virtual environment located at `./venv`
- Always use `./venv/bin/python` instead of `python` or `python3` when running Python commands
- Always use `./venv/bin/pip` instead of `pip` or `pip3` when installing packages
- Always use `./venv/bin/alembic` instead of `alembic` when running migrations
- Example: `./venv/bin/python -c "import app.config"` instead of `python3 -c "import app.config"`

